  <Annotation SID="2271">
    <P Name="Name">&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; font-family:&apos;Helvetica&apos;; font-size:10px; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;The Suspension Forces Additional block can be used in addition or instead of the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;the standard blocks of the CreateBus Suspension Forces block in the following cases:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol type=&quot;I&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;&quot;&gt;&lt;li align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:11px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;In Addition: The user model integrated in the CreateBus Suspension Forces Additional block is to be superposed with the model specified on the Suspension Forces level&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:11px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;Instead of: The sorting of the force signals of the user model is done by force element type (e.g. Buffer) in the order of the wheel carriers (e.g. Buffer FL, Buffer FR, ...). In this case the signals of the CreateBus Suspension Forces block need to be disabled e.g. by manually connecting them to ground signals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10px; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;ATTENTION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10px;&quot;&gt;: The forces given in the CreateBus Suspension Forces Additional block are internally added to the forces of the Suspension Forces block. If this is not desired, make sure to include a force model only in one of the two levels.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</P>
    <P Name="Position">[13, 183, 413, 367]</P>
    <P Name="InternalMargins">[0, 0, 0, 0]</P>
    <P Name="FixedWidth">on</P>
    <P Name="Interpreter">rich</P>
    <P Name="ZOrder">-1</P>
  </Annotation>
</System>

